                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(center)\">\n                <persName>WOLF, HART &amp; CO.</persName>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"align(center)\"><placeName>LAW AND COLLECTION OFFICE</placeName>,</p>\n            <p rend=\"align(center)\"><placeName>Rooms 5 and 6, Washington Building</placeName>,</p>\n            <p rend=\"align(center)\"><placeName>CORNER SEVENTH STREET AND PENN\n                AVENUE</placeName>,</p>\n            <p rend=\"align(right)\"><placeName>Washington, D.C</placeName>, <date>Feby 18th,\n                    1867</date></p>\n            <p><placeName>Lock Box 51</placeName>.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">\n                <addressee>Rev Isaac Leeser</addressee>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(2)\">My Dear Sir</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(3)\">Our mutual friend<lb/>\n                <persName>Solomon</persName> handed me your interesting<lb/> letter, in answer\n                thereto I would respe<lb/>ctfully say that the oath taken<lb/> by attys in this\n                District has been<lb/> changed since the War, the one<lb/> alluded to in the\n                    M<add>?</add> trial<lb/> alludes to the oath taken <hi rend=\"underline\"\n                    >prior</hi> to the<lb/> War. Do you suppose for a<lb/> moment that I would take\n                such?<lb/> or that I would rest until repea<lb/>led? I am informed however<lb/> that\n                in <placeName>Maryland</placeName> the Law still<lb/> exists, but that is not\n                strange</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3sj1b747/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
